21#define RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(x) \
22 if (!(x)) { \
23 return absl::nullopt; \
24 }
25
26namespace {
27const int kMaxPicInitQpDeltaValue = 25;
28const int kMinPicInitQpDeltaValue = -26;
29} // namespace
30
31namespace webrtc {

33// General note: this is based off the 02/2018 version of the H.265 standard.
34// You can find it on this page:
35// http://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-H.265
36
37absl::optional<H265PpsParser::PpsState> H265PpsParser::ParsePps(
38 const uint8_t* data,
39 size_t length) {
40 // First, parse out rbsp, which is basically the source buffer minus emulation
41 // bytes (the last byte of a 0x00 0x00 0x03 sequence). RBSP is defined in
42 // section 7.3.1 of the H.264 standard.
43 std::vector<uint8_t> unpacked_buffer = H264::ParseRbsp(data, length);
44 rtc::BitBuffer bit_buffer(unpacked_buffer.data(), unpacked_buffer.size());
45 return ParseInternal(&bit_buffer);
46}
47
48bool H265PpsParser::ParsePpsIds(const uint8_t* data,
49 size_t length,
50 uint32_t* pps_id,
51 uint32_t* sps_id) {
52 RTC_DCHECK(pps_id);
53 RTC_DCHECK(sps_id);
54 // First, parse out rbsp, which is basically the source buffer minus emulation
55 // bytes (the last byte of a 0x00 0x00 0x03 sequence). RBSP is defined in
56 // section 7.3.1 of the H.265 standard.
57 std::vector<uint8_t> unpacked_buffer = H264::ParseRbsp(data, length);
58 rtc::BitBuffer bit_buffer(unpacked_buffer.data(), unpacked_buffer.size());
59 return ParsePpsIdsInternal(&bit_buffer, pps_id, sps_id);
60}
61
62absl::optional<uint32_t> H265PpsParser::ParsePpsIdFromSliceSegmentLayerRbsp(
63 const uint8_t* data,
64 size_t length,
65 uint8_t nalu_type) {
66 rtc::BitBuffer slice_reader(data, length);
67
68 // first_slice_segment_in_pic_flag: u(1)
69 uint32_t first_slice_segment_in_pic_flag = 0;
70 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
71 slice_reader.ReadBits(&first_slice_segment_in_pic_flag, 1));
72
73 if (nalu_type >= H265::NaluType::kBlaWLp &&
74 nalu_type <= H265::NaluType::kRsvIrapVcl23) {
75 // no_output_of_prior_pics_flag: u(1)
76 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(slice_reader.ConsumeBits(1));
77 }
78
79 // slice_pic_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
80 uint32_t slice_pic_parameter_set_id = 0;
81 if (!slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(&slice_pic_parameter_set_id))
82 return absl::nullopt;
83
84 return slice_pic_parameter_set_id;
85}
86
87absl::optional<H265PpsParser::PpsState> H265PpsParser::ParseInternal(
88 rtc::BitBuffer* bit_buffer) {
89 PpsState pps;
90
91 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(ParsePpsIdsInternal(bit_buffer, &pps.id, &pps.sps_id));
92
93 uint32_t bits_tmp;
94 uint32_t golomb_ignored;
95 // entropy_coding_mode_flag: u(1)
96 uint32_t entropy_coding_mode_flag;
97 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(&entropy_coding_mode_flag, 1));
98 pps.entropy_coding_mode_flag = entropy_coding_mode_flag != 0;
99 // bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag: u(1)
100 uint32_t bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag;
101 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
102 bit_buffer->ReadBits(&bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag, 1));
103 pps.bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag =
104 bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag != 0;
105
106 // num_slice_groups_minus1: ue(v)
107 uint32_t num_slice_groups_minus1;
108 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
109 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&num_slice_groups_minus1));
110 if (num_slice_groups_minus1 > 0) {
111 uint32_t slice_group_map_type;
112 // slice_group_map_type: ue(v)
113 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
114 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&slice_group_map_type));
115 if (slice_group_map_type == 0) {
116 for (uint32_t i_group = 0; i_group <= num_slice_groups_minus1;
117 ++i_group) {
118 // run_length_minus1[iGroup]: ue(v)
119 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
120 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
121 }
122 } else if (slice_group_map_type == 1) {
123 // TODO(sprang): Implement support for dispersed slice group map type.
124 // See 8.2.2.2 Specification for dispersed slice group map type.
125 } else if (slice_group_map_type == 2) {
126 for (uint32_t i_group = 0; i_group <= num_slice_groups_minus1;
127 ++i_group) {
128 // top_left[iGroup]: ue(v)
129 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
130 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
131 // bottom_right[iGroup]: ue(v)
132 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
133 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
134 }
135 } else if (slice_group_map_type == 3 || slice_group_map_type == 4 ||
136 slice_group_map_type == 5) {
137 // slice_group_change_direction_flag: u(1)
138 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(&bits_tmp, 1));
139 // slice_group_change_rate_minus1: ue(v)
140 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
141 } else if (slice_group_map_type == 6) {
142 // pic_size_in_map_units_minus1: ue(v)
143 uint32_t pic_size_in_map_units_minus1;
144 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
145 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&pic_size_in_map_units_minus1));
146 uint32_t slice_group_id_bits = 0;
147 uint32_t num_slice_groups = num_slice_groups_minus1 + 1;
148 // If num_slice_groups is not a power of two an additional bit is required
149 // to account for the ceil() of log2() below.
150 if ((num_slice_groups & (num_slice_groups - 1)) != 0)
151 ++slice_group_id_bits;
152 while (num_slice_groups > 0) {
153 num_slice_groups >>= 1;
154 ++slice_group_id_bits;
155 }
156 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= pic_size_in_map_units_minus1; i++) {
157 // slice_group_id[i]: u(v)
158 // Represented by ceil(log2(num_slice_groups_minus1 + 1)) bits.
159 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
160 bit_buffer->ReadBits(&bits_tmp, slice_group_id_bits));
161 }
162 }
163 }
164 // num_ref_idx_l0_default_active_minus1: ue(v)
165 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
166 // num_ref_idx_l1_default_active_minus1: ue(v)
167 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
168 // weighted_pred_flag: u(1)
169 uint32_t weighted_pred_flag;
170 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(&weighted_pred_flag, 1));
171 pps.weighted_pred_flag = weighted_pred_flag != 0;
172 // weighted_bipred_idc: u(2)
173 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(&pps.weighted_bipred_idc, 2));
174
175 // pic_init_qp_minus26: se(v)
176 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
177 bit_buffer->ReadSignedExponentialGolomb(&pps.pic_init_qp_minus26));
178 // Sanity-check parsed value
179 if (pps.pic_init_qp_minus26 > kMaxPicInitQpDeltaValue ||
180 pps.pic_init_qp_minus26 < kMinPicInitQpDeltaValue) {
181 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(false);
182 }
183 // pic_init_qs_minus26: se(v)
184 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
185 // chroma_qp_index_offset: se(v)
186 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(&golomb_ignored));
187 // deblocking_filter_control_present_flag: u(1)
188 // constrained_intra_pred_flag: u(1)
189 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(&bits_tmp, 2));
190 // redundant_pic_cnt_present_flag: u(1)
191 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
192 bit_buffer->ReadBits(&pps.redundant_pic_cnt_present_flag, 1));
193
194 return pps;
195}
196
197bool H265PpsParser::ParsePpsIdsInternal(rtc::BitBuffer* bit_buffer,
198 uint32_t* pps_id,
199 uint32_t* sps_id) {
200 // pic_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
201 if (!bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(pps_id))
202 return false;
203 // seq_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
204 if (!bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(sps_id))
205 return false;
206 return true;
207}
